Document: VisualShaderNodeCurveTexture
Path: godot/classes/class_visualshadernodecurvetexture.rst
Summary: A visual shader node that applies a curve texture to modify color or other properties in a shader.

Inherits: VisualShaderNode < VisualShaderNodeTexture < VisualShaderNode
This node type is used in visual shaders to sample a curve texture, which can be used for color grading, gradient mapping, or other texture-based transformations. The curve texture is typically a 1D or 2D texture that defines a mapping between input and output values. When connected in a shader graph, this node outputs the sampled value from the curve texture based on the input parameter. The node supports various texture sampling modes and can be configured to use different channels of the texture for different purposes. It is commonly used in post-processing effects and material shading to create smooth transitions between colors or values.
